Pre-Game Insights: Germany's 21-year-old playmaker Jamal Musiala and Spain's 16-year-old winger Lamine Yamal are highlighted as key players for the match.
Musiala expressed his enjoyment of the responsibility and trust given by his coach, allowing him to play freely.
Spain's coach Luis de la Fuente gives Yamal similar freedom on the wing, paralleling Musiala's role.
Both Germany and Spain are considered the best two teams in the tournament so far.
Germany's confidence is boosted by their performance in the last 16 against Denmark, while Spain's confidence comes from their comeback against Georgia.
Spain's forward Dani Olmo acknowledged Germany as a tough opponent and expressed a preference to face them now rather than in the final.
